<exprlist>
  <COMMENT line1="1" col1="1" line2="1" col2="32" start="265" end="296">### Methods for the SCESet class</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="3" col1="1" line2="3" col2="80" start="793" end="872">################################################################################</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="4" col1="1" line2="4" col2="41" start="1057" end="1097">### constructor function for SCESet class</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="6" col1="1" line2="6" col2="30" start="1585" end="1614">#' Create a new SCESet object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="7" col1="1" line2="7" col2="2" start="1849" end="1850">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="8" col1="1" line2="8" col2="79" start="2113" end="2191">#' Create a new SCESet object (the basic data container class in scater) from a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="9" col1="1" line2="9" col2="76" start="2377" end="2452">#' supplied matrix of expression values, plus cell and feature metadata. The</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="10" col1="1" line2="10" col2="80" start="2641" end="2720">#' expression matrix have rows representing features (usually genes) and columns</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="11" col1="1" line2="11" col2="22" start="2905" end="2926">#' representing cells.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="12" col1="1" line2="12" col2="2" start="3169" end="3170">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="13" col1="1" line2="13" col2="79" start="3433" end="3511">#' @param exprsData expression data matrix for an experiment (features x cells)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="14" col1="1" line2="14" col2="70" start="3697" end="3766">#' @param countData data matrix containing raw count expression values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="15" col1="1" line2="15" col2="61" start="3961" end="4021">#' @param tpmData matrix of class \code{"numeric"} containing</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="16" col1="1" line2="16" col2="50" start="4225" end="4274">#' transcripts-per-million (TPM) expression values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="17" col1="1" line2="17" col2="76" start="4489" end="4564">#' @param fpkmData matrix of class \code{"numeric"} containing fragments per</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="18" col1="1" line2="18" col2="69" start="4753" end="4821">#' kilobase of exon per million reads mapped (FPKM) expression values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="19" col1="1" line2="19" col2="72" start="5017" end="5088">#' @param cpmData matrix of class \code{"numeric"} containing counts per</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="20" col1="1" line2="20" col2="45" start="5281" end="5325">#' million (CPM) expression values (optional)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="21" col1="1" line2="21" col2="72" start="5545" end="5616">#' @param phenoData data frame containing attributes of individual cells</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="22" col1="1" line2="22" col2="79" start="5809" end="5887">#' @param featureData data frame containing attributes of features (e.g. genes)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="23" col1="1" line2="23" col2="80" start="6073" end="6152">#' @param experimentData MIAME class object containing metadata data and details</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="24" col1="1" line2="24" col2="36" start="6337" end="6372">#' about the experiment and dataset.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="25" col1="1" line2="25" col2="75" start="6601" end="6675">#' @param is_exprsData matrix of class \code{"logical"}, indicating whether</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="26" col1="1" line2="26" col2="70" start="6865" end="6934">#'    or not each observation is above the \code{lowerDetectionLimit}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="27" col1="1" line2="27" col2="78" start="7129" end="7206">#' @param cellPairwiseDistances object of class \code{"dist"} (or a class that</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="28" col1="1" line2="28" col2="73" start="7393" end="7465">#' extends "dist") containing cell-cell distance or dissimilarity values.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="29" col1="1" line2="29" col2="81" start="7657" end="7737">#' @param featurePairwiseDistances object of class \code{"dist"} (or a class that</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="30" col1="1" line2="30" col2="79" start="7921" end="7999">#' extends "dist") containing feature-feature distance or dissimilarity values.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="31" col1="1" line2="31" col2="80" start="8185" end="8264">#' @param lowerDetectionLimit the minimum expression level that constitutes true</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="32" col1="1" line2="32" col2="71" start="8449" end="8519">#'  expression (defaults to zero and uses count data to determine if an</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="33" col1="1" line2="33" col2="37" start="8713" end="8749">#'  observation is expressed or not).</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="34" col1="1" line2="34" col2="77" start="8977" end="9053">#' @param logExprsOffset numeric scalar, providing the offset used when doing</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="35" col1="1" line2="35" col2="80" start="9241" end="9320">#' log2-transformations of expression data to avoid trying to take logs of zero.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="36" col1="1" line2="36" col2="36" start="9505" end="9540">#' Default offset value is \code{1}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="37" col1="1" line2="37" col2="2" start="9769" end="9770">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="38" col1="1" line2="38" col2="30" start="10033" end="10062">#' @return a new SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="39" col1="1" line2="39" col2="2" start="10297" end="10298">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="40" col1="1" line2="40" col2="11" start="10561" end="10571">#' @details</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="41" col1="1" line2="41" col2="76" start="10825" end="10900">#' Scater requires that all data be housed in SCESet objects. SCESet extends</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="42" col1="1" line2="42" col2="70" start="11089" end="11158">#' Bioconductor's ExpressionSet class, and the same basic interface is</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="43" col1="1" line2="43" col2="75" start="11353" end="11427">#' supported. newSCESet() expects a single matrix of expression values of a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="44" col1="1" line2="44" col2="79" start="11617" end="11695">#' nominated type to be provided, for example a matrix of counts or a matrix of</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="45" col1="1" line2="45" col2="70" start="11881" end="11950">#' transcripts-per-million values. There is a hierarchy applied to the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="46" col1="1" line2="46" col2="79" start="12145" end="12223">#' expression data: counts &gt; transcripts-per-million (tpm) &gt; counts-per-million</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="47" col1="1" line2="47" col2="80" start="12409" end="12488">#' (cpm) &gt; fragments-per-kilobase-per-million-mapped (fpkm) &gt; generic expression</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="48" col1="1" line2="48" col2="72" start="12673" end="12744">#' values on the log2 scale (exprs). Data types higher in the higher are</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="49" col1="1" line2="49" col2="76" start="12937" end="13012">#' preferred. Data types lower in the hierarchy will be computed from values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="50" col1="1" line2="50" col2="74" start="13201" end="13274">#' higher in the hierarchy - e.g. counts-per-million and expression values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="51" col1="1" line2="51" col2="77" start="13465" end="13541">#' (as log2(cpm + offset)) will be computed from counts. Data types higher in</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="52" col1="1" line2="52" col2="79" start="13729" end="13807">#' the hierarchy will never be computed from types lower in the hierarchy (e.g.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="53" col1="1" line2="53" col2="57" start="13993" end="14049">#' counts will never be computed from exprs values). At a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="54" col1="1" line2="54" col2="78" start="14257" end="14334">#' minimum, an SCESet object will contain exprs values; these will be computed</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="55" col1="1" line2="55" col2="73" start="14521" end="14593">#' as log2(*pm + offset) values if a data type higher in the hierarchy is</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="56" col1="1" line2="56" col2="37" start="14785" end="14821">#' supplied as the expression matrix.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="57" col1="1" line2="57" col2="2" start="15049" end="15050">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="58" col1="1" line2="58" col2="77" start="15313" end="15389">#' Per-feature and per-cell metadata can be supplied with the featureData and</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="59" col1="1" line2="59" col2="93" start="15577" end="15669">#' phenoData arguments, respectively. Use of these optional arguments is strongly encouraged.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="60" col1="1" line2="60" col2="2" start="15841" end="15842">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="61" col1="1" line2="61" col2="75" start="16105" end="16179">#' Many methods are provided in the package that operate on SCESet objects.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="62" col1="1" line2="62" col2="2" start="16369" end="16370">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="63" col1="1" line2="63" col2="79" start="16633" end="16711">#' Aside from the hierarchy of data types described above, scater is relatively</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="64" col1="1" line2="64" col2="74" start="16897" end="16970">#' agnostic with respect to data the nature of the expression values. Most</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="65" col1="1" line2="65" col2="78" start="17161" end="17238">#' frequently used values are feature counts or transcripts-per-million (tpm),</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="66" col1="1" line2="66" col2="77" start="17425" end="17501">#' but any valid output from a program that calculates expression values from</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="67" col1="1" line2="67" col2="75" start="17689" end="17763">#' RNA-Seq reads is supported. For example, expression values could also be</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="68" col1="1" line2="68" col2="66" start="17953" end="18018">#' values from a single cell qPCR run or some other type of assay.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="69" col1="1" line2="69" col2="2" start="18217" end="18218">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="70" col1="1" line2="70" col2="77" start="18481" end="18557">#' In some cases it may be desirable to have both tpm and counts in an SCESet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="71" col1="1" line2="71" col2="78" start="18745" end="18822">#' object. In such cases, expression matrices can be added to an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="72" col1="1" line2="72" col2="78" start="19009" end="19086">#' after it has been produced by using the \code{\link{set_exprs}} function to</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="73" col1="1" line2="73" col2="50" start="19273" end="19322">#' add the expression matrix to the SCESet object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="74" col1="1" line2="74" col2="2" start="19537" end="19538">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="75" col1="1" line2="75" col2="60" start="19801" end="19860">#' In many downstream functions it is most convenient if the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="76" col1="1" line2="76" col2="75" start="20065" end="20139">#' \code{'exprs'} values are on the log2-scale, so this is done by default.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="77" col1="1" line2="77" col2="2" start="20329" end="20330">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="78" col1="1" line2="78" col2="45" start="20593" end="20637">#' @importFrom Biobase annotatedDataFrameFrom</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="79" col1="1" line2="79" col2="41" start="20857" end="20897">#' @importFrom Biobase AnnotatedDataFrame</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="80" col1="1" line2="80" col2="35" start="21121" end="21155">#' @importFrom Biobase assayDataNew</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="81" col1="1" line2="81" col2="39" start="21385" end="21423">#' @importFrom Biobase assayDataElement</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="82" col1="1" line2="82" col2="32" start="21649" end="21680">#' @importFrom edgeR cpm.default</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="83" col1="1" line2="83" col2="18" start="21913" end="21930">#' @import methods</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="84" col1="1" line2="84" col2="10" start="22177" end="22186">#' @export</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="85" col1="1" line2="85" col2="12" start="22441" end="22452">#' @examples</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="86" col1="1" line2="86" col2="28" start="22705" end="22732">#' data("sc_example_counts")</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="87" col1="1" line2="87" col2="31" start="22969" end="22999">#' data("sc_example_cell_info")</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="88" col1="1" line2="88" col2="63" start="23233" end="23295">#' pd &lt;- new("AnnotatedDataFrame", data = sc_example_cell_info)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="89" col1="1" line2="89" col2="77" start="23497" end="23573">#' example_sceset &lt;- newSCESet(countData = sc_example_counts, phenoData = pd)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="90" col1="1" line2="90" col2="17" start="23761" end="23777">#' example_sceset</COMMENT>
  <expr line1="91" col1="1" line2="218" col2="1" start="24025" end="57553">

      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="92" col1="39" line2="92" col2="39" start="24327" end="24327">,</OP-COMMA>

      <EQ_FORMALS line1="93" col1="31" line2="93" col2="31" start="24583" end="24583">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="93" col1="33" line2="93" col2="36" start="24585" end="24588">
        <NULL_CONST line1="93" col1="33" line2="93" col2="36" start="24585" end="24588">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="93" col1="37" line2="93" col2="37" start="24589" end="24589">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="94" col1="23" line2="94" col2="30" start="24839" end="24846">fpkmData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="94" col1="32" line2="94" col2="32" start="24848" end="24848">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="94" col1="34" line2="94" col2="37" start="24850" end="24853">
        <NULL_CONST line1="94" col1="34" line2="94" col2="37" start="24850" end="24853">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="94" col1="38" line2="94" col2="38" start="24854" end="24854">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="95" col1="23" line2="95" col2="29" start="25103" end="25109">cpmData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="95" col1="31" line2="95" col2="31" start="25111" end="25111">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="95" col1="33" line2="95" col2="36" start="25113" end="25116">
        <NULL_CONST line1="95" col1="33" line2="95" col2="36" start="25113" end="25116">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="95" col1="37" line2="95" col2="37" start="25117" end="25117">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="96" col1="23" line2="96" col2="31" start="25367" end="25375">phenoData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="96" col1="33" line2="96" col2="33" start="25377" end="25377">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="96" col1="35" line2="96" col2="38" start="25379" end="25382">
        <NULL_CONST line1="96" col1="35" line2="96" col2="38" start="25379" end="25382">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="96" col1="39" line2="96" col2="39" start="25383" end="25383">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="97" col1="23" line2="97" col2="33" start="25631" end="25641">featureData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="97" col1="35" line2="97" col2="35" start="25643" end="25643">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="97" col1="37" line2="97" col2="40" start="25645" end="25648">
        <NULL_CONST line1="97" col1="37" line2="97" col2="40" start="25645" end="25648">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="97" col1="41" line2="97" col2="41" start="25649" end="25649">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="98" col1="23" line2="98" col2="36" start="25895" end="25908">experimentData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="98" col1="38" line2="98" col2="38" start="25910" end="25910">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="98" col1="40" line2="98" col2="43" start="25912" end="25915">
        <NULL_CONST line1="98" col1="40" line2="98" col2="43" start="25912" end="25915">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="98" col1="44" line2="98" col2="44" start="25916" end="25916">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="99" col1="23" line2="99" col2="34" start="26159" end="26170">is_exprsData</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="99" col1="36" line2="99" col2="36" start="26172" end="26172">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="99" col1="38" line2="99" col2="41" start="26174" end="26177">
        <NULL_CONST line1="99" col1="38" line2="99" col2="41" start="26174" end="26177">NULL</NULL_CONST>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="99" col1="42" line2="99" col2="42" start="26178" end="26178">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="100" col1="23" line2="100" col2="43" start="26423" end="26443">cellPairwiseDistances</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="100" col1="45" line2="100" col2="45" start="26445" end="26445">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="100" col1="47" line2="100" col2="60" start="26447" end="26460">
        <expr line1="100" col1="47" line2="100" col2="50" start="26447" end="26450">
          <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="100" col1="47" line2="100" col2="50" start="26447" end="26450">dist</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
        </expr>
        <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="100" col1="51" line2="100" col2="51" start="26451" end="26451">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
        <expr line1="100" col1="52" line2="100" col2="59" start="26452" end="26459">
          <expr line1="100" col1="52" line2="100" col2="57" start="26452" end="26457">
            <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="100" col1="52" line2="100" col2="57" start="26452" end="26457">vector</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
          </expr>
          <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="100" col1="58" line2="100" col2="58" start="26458" end="26458">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>

        </expr>
        <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="100" col1="60" line2="100" col2="60" start="26460" end="26460">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="100" col1="61" line2="100" col2="61" start="26461" end="26461">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="101" col1="23" line2="101" col2="46" start="26687" end="26710">featurePairwiseDistances</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
      <EQ_FORMALS line1="101" col1="48" line2="101" col2="48" start="26712" end="26712">=</EQ_FORMALS>
      <expr line1="101" col1="50" line2="101" col2="63" start="26714" end="26727">
        <expr line1="101" col1="50" line2="101" col2="53" start="26714" end="26717">
          <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="101" col1="50" line2="101" col2="53" start="26714" end="26717">dist</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
        </expr>
        <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="101" col1="54" line2="101" col2="54" start="26718" end="26718">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
        <expr line1="101" col1="55" line2="101" col2="62" start="26719" end="26726">
          <expr line1="101" col1="55" line2="101" col2="60" start="26719" end="26724">
            <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="101" col1="55" line2="101" col2="60" start="26719" end="26724">vector</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
          </expr>
          <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="101" col1="61" line2="101" col2="61" start="26725" end="26725">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
          <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="101" col1="62" line2="101" col2="62" start="26726" end="26726">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
        </expr>
        <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="101" col1="63" line2="101" col2="63" start="26727" end="26727">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
      </expr>

  <COMMENT line1="337" col1="1" line2="337" col2="31" start="88969" end="88999">### subsetting an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="339" col1="1" line2="339" col2="28" start="89497" end="89524">#' Subsetting SCESet Objects</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="340" col1="1" line2="340" col2="2" start="89761" end="89762">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="341" col1="1" line2="341" col2="76" start="90025" end="90100">#' Subset method for SCESet objects, which subsets both the expression data,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="342" col1="1" line2="342" col2="62" start="90289" end="90350">#' phenotype data, feature data and other slots in the object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="343" col1="1" line2="343" col2="2" start="90553" end="90554">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="344" col1="1" line2="344" col2="27" start="90817" end="90843">#' @return an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="345" col1="1" line2="345" col2="24" start="91081" end="91104">#' @rdname SCESet-subset</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="346" col1="1" line2="346" col2="22" start="91345" end="91366">#' @name SCESet-subset</COMMENT>
  <expr line1="347" col1="1" line2="347" col2="4" start="91609" end="91612">
    <NULL_CONST line1="347" col1="1" line2="347" col2="4" start="91609" end="91612">NULL</NULL_CONST>
  </expr>
  <COMMENT line1="349" col1="1" line2="349" col2="31" start="92137" end="92167">#' @inheritParams base::Extract</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="350" col1="1" line2="350" col2="76" start="92401" end="92476">#' @param i,j,... indices specifying elements to extract or replace. Indices</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="351" col1="1" line2="351" col2="78" start="92665" end="92742">#' are numeric or character vectors or empty (missing) or \code{NULL}. Numeric</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="352" col1="1" line2="352" col2="80" start="92929" end="93008">#' values are coerced to integer as by \code{\link[base]{as.integer}} (and hence</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="353" col1="1" line2="353" col2="77" start="93193" end="93269">#' truncated towards zero). Character vectors will be matched to the names of</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="354" col1="1" line2="354" col2="57" start="93457" end="93513">#' the object (or for matrices/arrays, the dimnames): see</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="355" col1="1" line2="355" col2="51" start="93721" end="93771">#' \code{\link[base]{Extract}} for further details.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="356" col1="1" line2="356" col2="2" start="93985" end="93986">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="357" col1="1" line2="357" col2="82" start="94249" end="94330">#' For \code{[}-indexing only: \code{i, j, ...} can be logical vectors, indicating</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="358" col1="1" line2="358" col2="77" start="94513" end="94589">#' elements/slices to select. Such vectors are recycled if necessary to match</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="359" col1="1" line2="359" col2="76" start="94777" end="94852">#' the corresponding extent. \code{i, j, ...} can also be negative integers,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="360" col1="1" line2="360" col2="74" start="95041" end="95114">#' indicating elements/slices to leave out of the selection. When indexing</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="361" col1="1" line2="361" col2="78" start="95305" end="95382">#' arrays by \code{[} a single argument i can be a matrix with as many columns</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="362" col1="1" line2="362" col2="72" start="95569" end="95640">#' as there are dimensions of \code{x}; the result is then a vector with</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="363" col1="1" line2="363" col2="76" start="95833" end="95908">#' elements corresponding to the sets of indices in each row of \code{i}. An</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="364" col1="1" line2="364" col2="73" start="96097" end="96169">#' index value of \code{NULL} is treated as if it were \code{integer(0)}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="365" col1="1" line2="365" col2="2" start="96361" end="96362">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="580" col1="1" line2="580" col2="13" start="153121" end="153133">### get_exprs</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="582" col1="1" line2="582" col2="62" start="153649" end="153710">#' Generic accessor for expression data from an SCESet object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="583" col1="1" line2="583" col2="2" start="153913" end="153914">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="584" col1="1" line2="584" col2="80" start="154177" end="154256">#' Access by name a matrix of expression values, one row for each feature (gene,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="585" col1="1" line2="585" col2="76" start="154441" end="154516">#' exon, region, etc), and one column for each cell stored an element of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="586" col1="1" line2="586" col2="39" start="154705" end="154743">#' assayData slot of the SCESet object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="587" col1="1" line2="587" col2="2" start="154969" end="154970">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="588" col1="1" line2="588" col2="9" start="155233" end="155241">#' @usage</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="589" col1="1" line2="589" col2="69" start="155497" end="155565">#' \S4method{get_exprs}{SCESet}(object, exprs_values, warning = TRUE)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="590" col1="1" line2="590" col2="2" start="155761" end="155762">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="591" col1="1" line2="591" col2="19" start="156025" end="156043">#' @docType methods</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="592" col1="1" line2="592" col2="18" start="156289" end="156306">#' @name get_exprs</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="593" col1="1" line2="593" col2="20" start="156553" end="156572">#' @rdname get_exprs</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="594" col1="1" line2="594" col2="45" start="156817" end="156861">#' @aliases get_exprs get_exprs,SCESet-method</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="595" col1="1" line2="595" col2="2" start="157081" end="157082">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="596" col1="1" line2="596" col2="40" start="157345" end="157384">#' @param object a \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="597" col1="1" line2="597" col2="78" start="157609" end="157686">#' @param exprs_values character string indicating which values should be used</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="598" col1="1" line2="598" col2="75" start="157873" end="157947">#' as the expression values for this plot. Valid arguments are \code{"tpm"}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="599" col1="1" line2="599" col2="63" start="158137" end="158199">#' (transcripts per million), \code{"norm_tpm"} (normalised TPM</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="600" col1="1" line2="600" col2="76" start="158401" end="158476">#' values), \code{"fpkm"} (FPKM values), \code{"norm_fpkm"} (normalised FPKM</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="601" col1="1" line2="601" col2="76" start="158665" end="158740">#' values), \code{"counts"} (counts for each feature), \code{"norm_counts"},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="602" col1="1" line2="602" col2="67" start="158929" end="158995">#' \code{"cpm"} (counts-per-million), \code{"norm_cpm"} (normalised</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="603" col1="1" line2="603" col2="78" start="159193" end="159270">#' counts-per-million), \code{"exprs"} (whatever is in the \code{'exprs'} slot</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="604" col1="1" line2="604" col2="73" start="159457" end="159529">#' of the \code{SCESet} object; default), \code{"norm_exprs"} (normalised</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="605" col1="1" line2="605" col2="78" start="159721" end="159798">#' expression values) or \code{"stand_exprs"} (standardised expression values)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="606" col1="1" line2="606" col2="76" start="159985" end="160060">#' or any other slots that have been added to the \code{"assayData"} slot by</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="607" col1="1" line2="607" col2="12" start="160249" end="160260">#' the user.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="608" col1="1" line2="608" col2="73" start="160513" end="160585">#' @param warning a logical scalar specifying whether a warning should be</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="609" col1="1" line2="609" col2="75" start="160777" end="160851">#' raised, and \code{NULL} returned, if the requested expression values are</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="610" col1="1" line2="610" col2="68" start="161041" end="161108">#' not present in \code{object}. Otherwise, an error will be thrown.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="611" col1="1" line2="611" col2="65" start="161305" end="161369">#' @param ... further arguments passed to \code{get_exprs.SCESet}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="612" col1="1" line2="612" col2="25" start="161569" end="161593">#' @author Davis McCarthy</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="614" col1="1" line2="614" col2="12" start="162097" end="162108">#' @examples</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="618" col1="1" line2="618" col2="38" start="163153" end="163190">#' get_exprs(example_sceset, "counts")</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="619" col1="1" line2="619" col2="2" start="163417" end="163418">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="620" col1="1" line2="620" col2="43" start="163681" end="163723">#' ## new slots can be defined and accessed</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="621" col1="1" line2="621" col2="78" start="163945" end="164022">#' set_exprs(example_sceset, "scaled_counts") &lt;- t(t(counts(example_sceset)) /</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="624" col1="1" line2="624" col2="2" start="164737" end="164738">#'</COMMENT>
  <expr line1="625" col1="1" line2="638" col2="1" start="165001" end="168433">
    <expr line1="625" col1="1" line2="625" col2="16" start="165001" end="165016">

  <COMMENT line1="1303" col1="1" line2="1303" col2="46" start="343993" end="344038">#' Accessors size factors of an SCESet object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1304" col1="1" line2="1304" col2="2" start="344257" end="344258">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1305" col1="1" line2="1305" col2="78" start="344521" end="344598">#' For normalisation, library-specific size factors can be defined. Raw values</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1411" col1="1" line2="1411" col2="14" start="372505" end="372518">### bootstraps</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1413" col1="1" line2="1413" col2="69" start="373033" end="373101">#' Accessor and replacement for bootstrap results in an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1414" col1="1" line2="1414" col2="2" start="373297" end="373298">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1415" col1="1" line2="1415" col2="80" start="373561" end="373640">#' SCESet objects can contain an of bootstrap expression values (for example, as</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1416" col1="1" line2="1416" col2="79" start="373825" end="373903">#' generated by the kallisto software for quantifying feature abundance). These</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1417" col1="1" line2="1417" col2="81" start="374089" end="374169">#'  functions conveniently access and replace the 'bootstrap' slot with the value</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1418" col1="1" line2="1418" col2="74" start="374353" end="374426">#'  supplied, which must be an matrix of the correct size, namely the same</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1419" col1="1" line2="1419" col2="70" start="374617" end="374686">#'  number of rows and columns as the \code{SCEset} object as a whole.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1420" col1="1" line2="1420" col2="2" start="374881" end="374882">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1421" col1="1" line2="1421" col2="19" start="375145" end="375163">#' @docType methods</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1422" col1="1" line2="1422" col2="19" start="375409" end="375427">#' @name bootstraps</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1423" col1="1" line2="1423" col2="21" start="375673" end="375693">#' @rdname bootstraps</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1424" col1="1" line2="1424" col2="80" start="375937" end="376016">#' @aliases bootstraps bootstraps,SCESet-method bootstraps&lt;-,SCESet,array-method</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1425" col1="1" line2="1425" col2="2" start="376201" end="376202">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1426" col1="1" line2="1426" col2="40" start="376465" end="376504">#' @param object a \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1427" col1="1" line2="1427" col2="71" start="376729" end="376799">#' @param value an array of class \code{"numeric"} containing bootstrap</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1428" col1="1" line2="1428" col2="20" start="376993" end="377012">#' expression values</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1471" col1="1" line2="1471" col2="20" start="388345" end="388364">### reducedDimension</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1473" col1="1" line2="1473" col2="65" start="388873" end="388937">#' Reduced dimension representation for cells in an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1474" col1="1" line2="1474" col2="2" start="389137" end="389138">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1475" col1="1" line2="1475" col2="75" start="389401" end="389475">#' SCESet objects can contain a matrix of reduced dimension coordinates for</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1476" col1="1" line2="1476" col2="79" start="389665" end="389743">#' cells. These functions conveniently access and replace the reduced dimension</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1477" col1="1" line2="1477" col2="77" start="389929" end="390005">#' coordinates with the value supplied, which must be a matrix of the correct</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1478" col1="1" line2="1478" col2="59" start="390193" end="390251">#' size. The function \code{redDim} is simply shorthand for</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1479" col1="1" line2="1479" col2="27" start="390457" end="390483">#' \code{reducedDimension}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1480" col1="1" line2="1480" col2="2" start="390721" end="390722">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1575" col1="1" line2="1575" col2="81" start="415801" end="415881">#' SCESet objects can contain a matrix of pairwise distances between cells. These</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1576" col1="1" line2="1576" col2="88" start="416065" end="416152">#'  functions conveniently access and replace the cell pairwise distances with the value</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1577" col1="1" line2="1577" col2="86" start="416329" end="416414">#'  supplied, which must be a matrix of the correct size. The function \code{cellDist}</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1584" col1="1" line2="1584" col2="2" start="418177" end="418178">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1686" col1="1" line2="1686" col2="47" start="445105" end="445151">#' featurePairwiseDistances in an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1687" col1="1" line2="1687" col2="2" start="445369" end="445370">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1688" col1="1" line2="1688" col2="77" start="445633" end="445709">#' SCESet objects can contain a matrix of pairwise distances between features</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1689" col1="1" line2="1689" col2="77" start="445897" end="445973">#' (e.g. genes, transcripts). These functions conveniently access and replace</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1690" col1="1" line2="1690" col2="78" start="446161" end="446238">#' the gene pairwise distances with the value supplied, which must be a matrix</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1691" col1="1" line2="1691" col2="76" start="446425" end="446500">#' of the correct size. The function \code{featDist} is simply shorthand for</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1692" col1="1" line2="1692" col2="35" start="446689" end="446723">#' \code{featurePairwiseDistances}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1693" col1="1" line2="1693" col2="2" start="446953" end="446954">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1694" col1="1" line2="1694" col2="40" start="447217" end="447256">#' @param object a \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1695" col1="1" line2="1695" col2="78" start="447481" end="447558">#' @param value a matrix of class \code{"numeric"} containing feature pairwise</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1696" col1="1" line2="1696" col2="12" start="447745" end="447756">#' distances</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1697" col1="1" line2="1697" col2="2" start="448009" end="448010">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1698" col1="1" line2="1698" col2="19" start="448273" end="448291">#' @docType methods</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1850" col1="1" line2="1850" col2="11" start="488401" end="488411">### isSpike</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1852" col1="1" line2="1852" col2="44" start="488929" end="488972">#' Get spike-in features in an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1853" col1="1" line2="1853" col2="2" start="489193" end="489194">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1854" col1="1" line2="1854" col2="72" start="489457" end="489528">#' Get the features in the SCESet object that are spike-in controls, as </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1855" col1="1" line2="1855" col2="42" start="489721" end="489762">#' specified using \code{\link{setSpike}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1856" col1="1" line2="1856" col2="2" start="489985" end="489986">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1857" col1="1" line2="1857" col2="40" start="490249" end="490288">#' @param object a \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1858" col1="1" line2="1858" col2="82" start="490513" end="490594">#' @param type a character vector specifying the feature control sets to use. All </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1859" col1="1" line2="1859" col2="84" start="490777" end="490860">#' specified spike-in sets in \code{featureControlInfo(object)} are used by default.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1860" col1="1" line2="1860" col2="76" start="491041" end="491116">#' @param warning A logical scalar specifying if a warning should be raised </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1861" col1="1" line2="1861" col2="40" start="491305" end="491344">#' if spike-in controls are unavailable.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1862" col1="1" line2="1862" col2="71" start="491569" end="491639">#' @param ... arguments passed through generic version of the function.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1863" col1="1" line2="1863" col2="2" start="491833" end="491834">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1864" col1="1" line2="1864" col2="19" start="492097" end="492115">#' @docType methods</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1865" col1="1" line2="1865" col2="16" start="492361" end="492376">#' @name isSpike</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1866" col1="1" line2="1866" col2="18" start="492625" end="492642">#' @rdname isSpike</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1867" col1="1" line2="1867" col2="42" start="492889" end="492930">#' @aliases isSpike isSpike,SCESet-method </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1868" col1="1" line2="1868" col2="2" start="493153" end="493154">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1925" col1="1" line2="1925" col2="12" start="508201" end="508212">### setSpike</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1927" col1="1" line2="1927" col2="44" start="508729" end="508772">#' Set spike-in features in an SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1928" col1="1" line2="1928" col2="2" start="508993" end="508994">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1929" col1="1" line2="1929" col2="80" start="509257" end="509336">#' Specify which feature control sets in the SCESet object are spike-ins, i.e., </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1930" col1="1" line2="1930" col2="77" start="509521" end="509597">#' RNA of the same type and quantity added to each cell during the scRNA-seq </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1931" col1="1" line2="1931" col2="12" start="509785" end="509796">#' protocol.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1932" col1="1" line2="1932" col2="2" start="510049" end="510050">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1933" col1="1" line2="1933" col2="40" start="510313" end="510352">#' @param object a \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1934" col1="1" line2="1934" col2="78" start="510577" end="510654">#' @param value a character vector containing the names of the feature control</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1935" col1="1" line2="1935" col2="81" start="510841" end="510921">#' sets that are spike-ins. If \code{NULL}, all spike-in information is removed. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1936" col1="1" line2="1936" col2="71" start="511105" end="511175">#' @param ... arguments passed through generic version of the function.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1937" col1="1" line2="1937" col2="2" start="511369" end="511370">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1938" col1="1" line2="1938" col2="12" start="511633" end="511644">#' @details </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1939" col1="1" line2="1939" col2="121" start="511897" end="512017">#' While it is possible to declare overlapping sets as the spike-in sets with \code{isSpike(x)&lt;-}, this is not advisable.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1940" col1="1" line2="1940" col2="156" start="512161" end="512316">#' This is because some downstream operations assume that each row belongs to only one set (i.e., one of the spike-in sets, or the set of endogenous genes).</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1941" col1="1" line2="1941" col2="135" start="512425" end="512559">#' For example, normalization will use size factors from only one of the sets, so correspondence to multiple sets will not be honoured.</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1944" col1="1" line2="1944" col2="19" start="513217" end="513235">#' @docType methods</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="2204" col1="1" line2="2204" col2="23" start="581857" end="581879">#' Merge SCESet objects</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2205" col1="1" line2="2205" col2="2" start="582121" end="582122">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2206" col1="1" line2="2206" col2="92" start="582385" end="582476">#' Merge two SCESet objects that have the same features but contain different cells/samples.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2207" col1="1" line2="2207" col2="2" start="582649" end="582650">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2208" col1="1" line2="2208" col2="42" start="582913" end="582954">#' @param x an \code{\link{SCESet}} object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2209" col1="1" line2="2209" col2="42" start="583177" end="583218">#' @param y an \code{\link{SCESet}} object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2210" col1="1" line2="2210" col2="79" start="583441" end="583519">#' @param fdata_cols a character vector indicating which columns of featureData</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2211" col1="1" line2="2211" col2="77" start="583705" end="583781">#' of \code{x} and \code{y} should be retained. Alternatively, an integer or </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2212" col1="1" line2="2212" col2="80" start="583969" end="584048">#' logical vector can be supplied to subset the column names of \code{fData(x)},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2213" col1="1" line2="2213" col2="80" start="584233" end="584312">#' such that the subsetted character vector contains the columns to be retained.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2214" col1="1" line2="2214" col2="78" start="584497" end="584574">#' Defaults to all shared columns between \code{fData(x)} and \code{fData(y)}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2215" col1="1" line2="2215" col2="77" start="584761" end="584837">#' @param pdata_cols a character vector indicating which columns of phenoData</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2216" col1="1" line2="2216" col2="76" start="585025" end="585100">#' of \code{x} and \code{y} should be retained. Alternatively, an integer or</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2217" col1="1" line2="2217" col2="76" start="585289" end="585364">#' logical vector to subset the column names of \code{pData(x)}. Defaults to</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2218" col1="1" line2="2218" col2="66" start="585553" end="585618">#' all shared columns between \code{pData(x)} and \code{pData(y)}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2219" col1="1" line2="2219" col2="2" start="585817" end="585818">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2220" col1="1" line2="2220" col2="141" start="586081" end="586221">#' @details Existing cell-cell pairwise distances and feature-feature pairwise distances will not be valid for a merged \code{SCESet} object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2221" col1="1" line2="2221" col2="77" start="586345" end="586421">#' These entries are subsequently set to \code{NULL} in the returned object. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2222" col1="1" line2="2222" col2="83" start="586609" end="586691">#' Similarly, new \code{experimentData} will need to be added to the merged object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2223" col1="1" line2="2223" col2="3" start="586873" end="586875">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2224" col1="1" line2="2224" col2="134" start="587137" end="587270">#' If \code{fdata_cols} does not include the definition of feature controls, the control sets may not be defined in the output object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2225" col1="1" line2="2225" col2="137" start="587401" end="587537">#' In such cases, a warning is issued and the undefined control sets are removed from the \code{featureControlInfo} of the merged object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2226" col1="1" line2="2226" col2="2" start="587665" end="587666">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="2228" col1="1" line2="2228" col2="138" start="588193" end="588330">#' For arbitrary \code{x} and \code{y}, there is no guarantee that the size factors (and thus \code{exprs}) are comparable across objects.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2229" col1="1" line2="2229" col2="2" start="588457" end="588458">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="2324" col1="1" line2="2324" col2="14" start="613537" end="613550">## writeSCESet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2326" col1="1" line2="2326" col2="41" start="614065" end="614105">#' Write an SCESet object to an HDF5 file</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2327" col1="1" line2="2327" col2="2" start="614329" end="614330">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2328" col1="1" line2="2328" col2="66" start="614593" end="614658">#' @param object \code{\link{SCESet}} object to be writted to file</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2329" col1="1" line2="2329" col2="75" start="614857" end="614931">#' @param file_path path to written file containing data from SCESet object</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2330" col1="1" line2="2330" col2="82" start="615121" end="615202">#' @param type character string indicating type of output file. Default is "HDF5".</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2331" col1="1" line2="2331" col2="79" start="615385" end="615463">#' @param overwrite_existing logical, if a file of the same name already exists</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2332" col1="1" line2="2332" col2="53" start="615649" end="615701">#' should it be overwritten? Default is \code{FALSE}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2333" col1="1" line2="2333" col2="2" start="615913" end="615914">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2334" col1="1" line2="2334" col2="80" start="616177" end="616256">#' @details Currently writing to HDF5 files is supported. The \pkg{\link{rhdf5}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2335" col1="1" line2="2335" col2="79" start="616441" end="616519">#' package is used to write data to file and can be used to read data from HDF5</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2336" col1="1" line2="2336" col2="67" start="616705" end="616771">#' files into R. For further details about the HDF5 data format see</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2337" col1="1" line2="2337" col2="44" start="616969" end="617012">#' \url{https://support.hdfgroup.org/HDF5/}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2338" col1="1" line2="2338" col2="2" start="617233" end="617234">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2339" col1="1" line2="2339" col2="82" start="617497" end="617578">#' @return Return is \code{NULL}, having written the \code{SCESet} object to file.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="2340" col1="1" line2="2340" col2="10" start="617761" end="617770">#' @export</COMMENT>
